From git@z Thu Jan  1 00:00:00 1970
From: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
Date: Wed, 02 Apr 2026 12:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] RDMAionic: Force carrier on in loopback mode for
 RDMA port activation

The sysfs loopback_mode attribute (patch 0018) sends the
IONIC_PORT_ATTR_LOOPBACK command to firmware, but the DSC
firmware does not synthesize a link-up event when no cable
is connected.  The kernel link_status_check reads the
firmware's port status and calls netif_carrier_on/off
accordingly -- so the link stays DOWN even in loopback
mode.

The RDMA port state (ionic_ibdev.c query_port) checks
netif_carrier_ok() to report IB_PORT_ACTIVE.  Without
carrier, RDMA QP transitions to RTR fail and all RDMA
loopback testing is blocked.

Fix by:
- Adding a loopback_mode field to struct ionic to track
  the current loopback state.
- Forcing netif_carrier_on() in loopback_mode_store
  when a non-zero mode is set.
- Skipping netif_carrier_off() in ionic_link_status_check
  when loopback_mode is active, preventing the periodic
  watchdog from overriding the forced carrier.
- Requesting a normal link status re-evaluation when
  loopback is disabled (mode 0).

Signed-off-by: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
---
 .../net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic.h       |  1 +
 .../ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_bus_pci.c   | 19 ++++++++++++++
 .../net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_lif.c   |  5 ++++
 3 files changed, 25 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic.h
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic.h
@@ -66,6 +66,7 @@ struct ionic {
 	struct timer_list watchdog_timer;
 	int watchdog_period;
+	u8 loopback_mode;
 };

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_bus_pci.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_bus_pci.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_bus_pci.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_bus_pci.c
 static ssize_t loopback_mode_store(...)
 {
 	struct ionic *ionic = ...;
+	struct ionic_lif *lif = ionic->lif;
+	struct net_device *netdev = lif ? lif->netdev : NULL;
 	...
 	err = ionic_dev_cmd_wait(ionic, DEVCMD_TIMEOUT);
 	mutex_unlock(&ionic->dev_cmd_lock);

+	if (!err)
+		ionic->loopback_mode = (u8)mode;
+
+	if (!err && netdev) {
+		if (mode) {
+			/* Force carrier on so the RDMA port
+			 * reports IB_PORT_ACTIVE.  Firmware
+			 * does not synthesize a link-up event
+			 * in loopback mode without a cable. */
+			netif_carrier_on(netdev);
+		} else {
+			/* Re-evaluate real link state */
+			ionic_link_status_check_request(lif,
+							true);
+		}
+	}
+
 	return err ? err : count;
 }

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_lif.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_lif.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_lif.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_lif.c
 static void ionic_link_status_check(...)
 {
 	...
 	} else {
+		/* Don't take carrier down if loopback mode
+		 * is active -- firmware reports link DOWN
+		 * without a cable even in loopback. */
+		if (lif->ionic->loopback_mode) {
+			clear_bit(IONIC_LIF_F_LINK_CHECK_REQUESTED, lif->state);
+			return;
+		}
+
 		if (netif_carrier_ok(netdev)) {
 			lif->link_down_count++;
